The '''Books of Massassi''' was a group of engraved tablets [[Writing/Legends|written]] by the [[Massassi/Legends|Massassi]] to cover their history.

==History==
Shortly after the establishment of the [[Jedi academy]] on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] in [[14 ABY/Legends|14 ABY]], the tablets were recovered from an underground passage sealed by a collapsed ceiling. [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Streen]] began the arduous task of translating them from the [[Massassi (language)|ancient language]] of the [[Massassi/Legends|Massassi]], and had completed his work on sixteen tablets by [[16 ABY/Legends|16 ABY]]. Within the texts, Streen found that the Massassi strove for perfection, unsated at their domination of Yavin 4. It was through this pursuit of perfection&mdash;or rather, power&mdash;that the Massassi were led down the path of the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] believed the texts to be from a singular author, a life work of essays describing Massassi history and religion. Some people believed the books to be the original sacred texts of the Massassi, recorded orally by educated [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]].

